name: integer_u16_minimum
description: |
  This is the minimum u16 value, 0. Subtracting 1 crosses the unsigned lower
  boundary and may trap, wrap to 65535, saturate, or be widened before
  evaluation. It is also an invalid divisor for integer division and remainder,
  making the pair with one useful for both underflow and divide-by-zero handling.
format: hex
decode-as: u16
pair:
  - with: one.input
    hint: tricky
  - with: ../i16/zero.input
    hint: tricky
tags:
  - "integer"
  - "unsigned-integer"
  - "u16"
  - "minimum"
  - "zero"
  - "boundary"
  - "underflow"
  - "division-by-zero"
  - "remainder-by-zero"
---
00 00 # 0
